The paper presents a novel computational approach for providing feedback at scale using generative descriptions of student cognition and probabilistic programs. This approach involves training inference networks to approximately parse real student solutions according to these generative models. The paper focuses on the application of this approach in the field of education, specifically in providing feedback to students. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are both related to the development of intelligent systems. The paper also involves natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the approach in a real classroom setting, which falls under cs.EDU (Education). Finally, the paper involves software engineering, specifically in the context of programming, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
